claim.claim-text:
An in vitro method for the expansion of a human precursor cell selected from the group consisting of a hematopoietic precursor cell, an epithelial precursor cell, a kidney precursor cell, a neural precursor cell, a skin precursor cell, a liver precursor cell, and a muscle cell, comprising the steps of (i) contacting the human precursor cell with an amount of an agonist of Notch function effective to inhibit differentiation of the human precursor cell, and (ii) exposing the human precursor cell to growth conditions such that the human precursor cell proliferates; where the cells are not derived from human embryos; and wherein the agonist of Notch function:
(i) is a Delta protein or comprises a fragment of a Delta protein, which fragment mediates binding to a Notch protein;
(ii) is a Serrate protein or comprises a fragment of a Serrate protein, which fragment mediates binding to a Notch protein;
(iii) is a Jagged protein or comprises a fragment of a Jagged protein, which fragment mediates binding to a Notch protein; or
(iv) is an antibody to a Notch protein or a fragment of the antibody containing the binding region.

